Tidekraken coiled through scalded straits, parrying cinder-threads and rift-remnants, to the Star Mountains' blaze-flooded abysses. There, Ignaraveil's veils merged rumble-rhythms with chart-anchors, spawning coils that overwhelmed harmony into vaporous deluge. "Why coil the boiling torrent?" flames crackled, mimicking Tidekraken's muffled roars. "To bank directed floods," she roared deeply, tentacles lashing like stag-horns, channeling excess with kraken-chants woven from fox-yips, lantern-flares, ember-blazes, phoenix-trills, river-sighs, trail-twists, gaze-pierces, moss-grips, current-binds, ash-veils, surge-rhythms, coil-evaporations, pyre-directions, draft-syncs, gale-horns, zephyr-talons, quake-fissures, moss-mists, root-binds, and veil-banks.

Coil grasped, Tidekraken tempered it into bounded tide, birthing the Banked Surge—floods nourishing without submersion. Zephyrstag exalted krakens as wardens of coiled potency. Their roars now harmonize swells, blending map, current, path, weave, tide, flame, mist, gaze, breath, trail, lantern, root, moss, anchor, ash, veil, surge, coil, rhythm, stride, pyre, draft, talon, sync, horn, gale, fissure, quake, ember, rumble, and flood. They affirm: surges flourish not in unbound deluges or parched voids, but in kraken-coils, banking force for harmony's vital currents.

